# Skill: Methodology Writing

## Structure for this paper's methodology
1. Dataset Construction
   - Collection pipeline (annotation platform -> export -> PaddleOCR format)
   - Book-level split rationale
   - Character dictionary construction
   - Preprocessing steps

2. Model Configurations
   - Baseline setup (what was NOT changed)
   - Fine-tuning setup (what WAS changed: epochs, lr, dict, layers)
   - LLM prompting strategy (exact prompt used)

3. Evaluation Protocol
   - CER/WER definitions
   - DER definition and formula: DER = diacritic_errors / total_diacritics
   - Minimal pair test set construction

## Writing rules
- State exact hyperparameters, not ranges ("lr=0.001", not "a small learning rate")
- Every design choice needs a one-sentence justification
- Write so another researcher could reproduce exactly
- Use past tense for what was done

## Reproducibility checklist (include in section)
- Hardware spec
- Training time
- Random seeds
- Framework versions
- Link to code/data release
